body:
I am not sure, but I think eliza has done something to the fetch method! Below I explain why!

I am trying to add the image upload feature to Twitter client. I have passed data as `agent-twitter-client` library accepts, but when I call it I get this error 
```
 {"errors":[{"code":38,"message":"media parameter is missing."}]}
```

I did extensive debugging. I cloned the `agent-twitter-client` and loaded it as a local dependency in eliza package.json.
```
        "agent-twitter-client": "file:/Users/amin/Downloads/agent-twitter-client",
```
I put some log at upload points in the `agent-twitter-client` and executed its tests that include image uploading. 
I could upload images by running this repo tests. But when I try to use it through eliza, I got the aforementioned error.

It's the upload point in the `agent-twitter-client`

```ts
    console.log({
      uploadUrl,
      p: {
        method: 'POST',
        headers,
        body: form,
      },
    });

    const response = await fetch(uploadUrl, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers,
      body: form,
    });
```

The console.log output is the same for running `agent-twitter-client` test and eliza agent running.
